<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9861> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9861" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/23> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "pp. 65-72" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9804> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9804" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/16> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 223" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8592> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8592" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 737" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3204> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3204" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Macrob. Sat. 3.14.14. It is not certain whether he continued to perform the duties of a Salius till his death. See 167." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3203> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3203" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Plut. TG 4.1. On his death before 129, see Cic. Rep. 1.31." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3202> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3202" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Plutarch states clearly that Gracchus was an Augur, but is not quite so explicit about Claudius, though it is probable that the banquet they attended together was an augural banquet ({Gr})." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3167> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3167" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Patrician. Probable member of the college of Augurs just before the death of Tiberius Gracchus in 133." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3166> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3166" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Plut. TG 4.1. A member of the college along with Ti. Gracchus, but when he entered is not known." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3163> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3163" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Elected under the agrarian law of Ti. Gracchus to resume possession of public land and divide it among the poor, then empowered to decide questions of ownership (App. BC 1.13, and 18-19; cf. CIL 1\n     .2.639-644 and 719, the boundary stones; Cic. Leg. Agr. 2.31; Liv. Per. 58; Val. Max. 7.2.6; Vell. 2.2.3; Plut. TG 13.1)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3110> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3110" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Willems (Sénat 1.113) holds that Scipio Nasica Serapio, Cos. 138, was chosen Princeps Senatus in 136, but the passage of Diodorus (34.33) on which he bases his argument has confused three generations of Nasicae. The evidence of Plutarch strongly indicates that Claudius was Princeps Senatus in 133." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3109> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3109" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap., Degrassi 52f., 125, 468f. ([Q. Fulv]ius M. f. M. n. Nobilior). Claudius exercised his office harshly but Fulvius was more moderate (Dio fr. 81; Fest. 360 L). Claudius was named Princeps Senatus (Plut. TG 4.1).\n     They completed the lustrum in 135 (Liv. Per. 56)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3034> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3034" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Macrob. 3.14.14; see 167, Salii." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3019> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3019" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap., Degrassi 52f., 125, 466f. (Ap. Clau[dius C. f. Ap. n. Pu]lcher, Q. Caeciliu[s Q. f. L. n. Metell.] Macedon.); Fast. Ant., ib. 160f. ([Ap. Clau]di P[ulcher], [Q. Caecili. M]et.); Liv. Oxy. Per. 53; Frontin. Aq. 1.7; Obseq. 21; Auct. Vir. Ill. 61.3; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Oros. 5.4.7; Cassiod.; and on Metellus, SIG\n     680; Val. Max. 7.1.1; 8.5.1. Claudius was assigned Italy, made war upon the Salassi, was defeated, but after the Decemviri at the command of the Sibylline books made an offering in enemy territory he was victorious (Liv. Per. 53; Dio fr. 74; Obseq. 21; Oros. 5.4.7). Being refused a triumph, he celebrated one on his own authority, foiling a tribunician veto by having his daughter, a Vestal, ride with him (Cic. Cael. 34; Val. Max. 5.4.6; Suet. Tib. 2; Dio fr. 74; Oros. 5.4.7; Macrob. Sat. 3.14.14; see Degrassi 558). Metellus was assigned Hither Spain, but{472} had first to subdue an uprising of slaves at Minturnae before he engaged in the Celtiberian war in Spain (Liv. Oxy. Per. 53; Val. Max. 9.3.7; App. Ib. 76; see Schulten, Gesch. Numantia 66f.; and 142, Promagistrates)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2983> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2983" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The latest date possible under the Lex Villia." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2806> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2806" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Macrob. Sat. 3.14.14. He must have become a Salius before his father's death in 167 (see Augurs, and Dion. Hal. 2.71)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10023> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10023" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Galleis Salasseis. MRR I.471-2, Itgenshorst no. 212, Rich no. 211." .
